\par\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s19\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang1046{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch 1.1. MetaReciclagem is not an "independent collective"}
\par\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s19\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang1046{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch 1.2. MetaReciclagem is not (and doesn't want to become) a formal NGO.}
\par\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s19\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang1046{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch 1.3. We are not }{\f0\fs24\lang1046{\*\listtag0}MetaReciclagem}
\par\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s19\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang1046{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch 1.4. We do MetaReciclagem}
\par\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s19\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang1046{\*\listtag0}
\par}\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s19\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang1046{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch I mean}
\par\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s19\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang1046{\*\listtag0}
\par}\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s19\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang1046{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch 1.5. MetaReciclagem is a name people use to identify some things they do.}
\par\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s19\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang1046{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch 1.6. More often than not, these things deal with reapropriation of technology.}
\par\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s19\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang1046{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch 1.7. More often than not, these actions aim social transformation.}
\par\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s19\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang1046{\*\listtag0}
\par}\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s19\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang1046{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch 1.8. Thus, in a decentralized, emergent way, }{\f0\fs24\lang1046{\*\listtag0}MetaReciclagem is a moement that aims social transformation through the reapropriation of technology.}
\par\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s19\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang1046{\*\listtag0}
\par}\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s19\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang1046{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch 2. Social technology}
\par\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s19\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang1046{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Social technology is not about hardware, the internet, weblogs, mailing lists or orkut}
\par\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s19\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang1046{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch It's about putting together people who have interests alike, and providing them the environment to interact, share knowledge, learn with each other and develop collective actions.}
\par\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s19\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang1046{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch Put in that way, computers are, indeed, social tehnology. But paper and a pencil, music, cantigas de roda and, well, language, are also social technology.}
\par\pard\plain\ltrpar\ql\s19\sl240\slmult1\itap0{\f0\fs24\lang1046{\*\listtag0}\abinodiroverride\ltrch That's why our approach to social technology is not based only on hardware or content. We tend to think over the social process that lies behind communication. People and people. }}